\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen.{\b  Alpini} Buchenau. Small or medium rhizomatous perennials. Leaves and bracts not pungent. Leaves often transversely septate, terete or canaliculate. Flowers in heads, usually strongly coloured and often large; involucral bracteoles absent. Filaments usually slender. Seeds with appendages.
