\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs, rarely annual. Leaves mostly basal, with closed sheath, without auricles, flat or canaliculate, usually with long, white cilia. Flowers in cymes, sometimes condensed into heads. Capsule 3-seeded; seeds usually with a basal appendage.
